================================================================================
OVERVIEW
================================================================================

This deposit contains all computational code used to process and analyse
single-nucleus RNA-sequencing (snRNA-seq) data from iPSC-derived miniature
brain organoids (miBrains) carrying the A53T alpha-synuclein mutation under
two APOE backgrounds (E3 and E4), compared to isogenic wild-type controls.

The study developed a 3D iPSC-based model integrating neurons, glia, myelin,
and cerebrovascular cells into a functional human brain tissue (miBrain).
snRNA-seq of miBrains confirmed the presence of diverse cell populations and
revealed cell-type-specific transcriptional responses to synuclein pathology,
including neuronal apoptotic/synaptic programs and astrocyte signatures of
lipid dysregulation and reactivity. APOE4 miBrains showed increased
pathogenic phosphorylation and aggregation of α-synuclein, driven by
cholesterol accumulation-induced lysosomal dysfunction in APOE4 astrocytes.

Interactive data exploration:
  UCSC Cell Browser: https://cells-test.gi.ucsc.edu/?ds=mibrain

A person external to the study team can use this code, together with the
deposited raw and processed datasets, to fully reproduce every result,
figure panel, and statistical table reported in the manuscript.


================================================================================
SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================

Hardware
--------
Steps 01–02 (Cell Ranger, preprocessing) were executed on a high-performance
computing (HPC) cluster (Mount Sinai Minerva; SLURM scheduler) with access
to ≥64 GB RAM per node and NVIDIA GPU nodes (optional, for Cell Ranger).
Steps 03–06 can be run on a workstation with ≥32 GB RAM.

Software — Python environment (steps 03–04)
--------------------------------------------
  Python          3.10+
  pegasus         1.9+       (pegasuspy; pip install pegasuspy)
  pegasusio       0.9+
  scanpy          1.9+
  anndata         0.9+
  numpy           1.24+
  pandas          2.0+
  scipy           1.11+
  seaborn         0.13+
  matplotlib      3.7+
  session_info    1.0+
  adjustText      0.8+

Install in one command:
  pip install pegasuspy scanpy anndata numpy pandas scipy seaborn matplotlib session_info adjustText

  pge (Pegasus Extras) — internal CommonMind/ISMMS package; not on PyPI.
      Provides: pb_agg_by_cluster, pearson_corr, spearman_corr, scanpy_hvf_h5ad,
      qc_boundary, ondisk_subset, read_everything_but_X, pge.save.
      Contact the corresponding author for access. See UTILITY MODULES section
      for guidance on replacing these calls if pge is unavailable.

Software — R environment (steps 05–06)
---------------------------------------
  R               4.3+
  Bioconductor    3.18+
  dreamlet        1.9+       (bioc: dreamlet)
  variancePartition           (bioc: variancePartition)
  zenith                      (bioc: zenith)
