  MSigDB v7.5.1 (KEGG, GO:BP, GO:MF)
  Download: https://www.gsea-msigdb.org/gsea/downloads.jsp


================================================================================
UTILITY MODULES (imported by notebooks — required)
================================================================================

utils.py
--------
Python module imported by 03_qc_preprocessing_annotation.ipynb via `from utils import *`.
Contains all core single-cell processing functions used in the preprocessing pipeline.

  read_10x_pegasus(inpath, outpath, sample)
      Reads a Cell Ranger filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5 file via Pegasus,
      attaches sample-level metadata (Sample, Channel, individualID), and
      writes per-sample .h5ad files.

  add_metadata(input, output, prefix)
      Merges Ensembl gene metadata (gene_type, Ensembl ID, chromosome) into
      adata.var from a local CSV (Human Ensembl metadata) and MitoCarta 3.0.
      Computes n_counts and n_features per cell.

  qc(input, output, prefix, args_mad_k=4, args_pct_mito=5, args_min_n_cells=50)
      Full QC pipeline: identifies robust genes (≥0.05% cells), flags mito/ribo/
      protein-coding/MitoCarta genes, applies MAD-based thresholds on nUMI and
      nGene (k=4 MADs), filters by percent_mito, and removes samples with fewer
      than args_min_n_cells cells. Saves QC diagnostic plots (histograms, scatter).

  log1p_norm(input, output)
      Shifted log1p normalisation (scanpy normalize_total → log1p). Stores raw
      counts in adata.layers["counts"] before transformation.

  sig_score(input, output)
      Computes Pegasus signature scores: cell cycle (G1/S, G2/M, cycle_diff),
      mitochondrial genes, ribosomal genes, and apoptosis. Used to regress out
      technical variation in PCA.

  run_global_clustering_umap(input_h5ad, output_h5ad, batch_key, ...)
      End-to-end dimensionality reduction pipeline:
        1. HVG selection (cell_ranger flavour, protein-coding autosomal genes,
           batch-aware via batch_key, n_top_genes=6000)
        2. PCA (n_pcs=30) with elbow plot
        3. Regression of n_counts, percent_mito, cycle_diff
        4. Harmony batch correction (rep=pca_regressed)
        5. kNN graph (K=100, L2 distance)
        6. UMAP (n_neighbors=100)
        7. Leiden clustering at resolutions 0.10 and 0.20
      Saves clustered AnnData (.h5ad) and UMAP figure.

  compute_cor(Mydata, agr_name, agr_file, pge_agr_path, cluster)
      Computes Pearson correlation between pseudobulk profiles of the miBRAIN
      data and a reference atlas aggregation CSV. Scales both matrices (z-score),
      maps best-hit annotation and score back to adata.obs, and renders a
      clustermap. Used for Leiden → cell-type label transfer.

  NOTE: utils.py imports `pge` (Pegasus Extras), a private Python package
  developed at the CommonMind Consortium / Icahn School of Medicine at Mount
  Sinai. The pge package provides: pb_agg_by_cluster(), pearson_corr(),
  spearman_corr(), scanpy_hvf_h5ad(), qc_boundary(), ondisk_subset(),
  read_everything_but_X(), and pge.save(). This package is not currently on
  PyPI. Contact the corresponding author for access, or replace these calls
  with equivalent scanpy/pegasus functions as documented in the inline comments.


utils_correlation.py
---------------------
Python module imported by 04_annotation_concordance_AMPPD.ipynb
via `from utils_correlation import *`.
Contains the full cross-dataset pseudobulk correlation pipeline.

  get_nominal_degs_fast(h5ad_file, cluster_label, p_thresh=0.05, ...)
      Stratified subsampling (max 500 cells/group) followed by Wilcoxon rank-sum
      test (scanpy rank_genes_groups). Returns genes significant at nominal p < 0.05
      (no multiple testing correction). Used as a feature-selection step only —
      not for reporting significance.

  get_fdr_degs_fast(h5ad_file, cluster_label, p_thresh=0.05, ...)
      Same as above but uses Benjamini-Hochberg adjusted p-values (pvals_adj).

  preprocess_for_correlation(df, scale="standard", min_variance_percentile=50)
      Variance percentile filter (removes bottom 50% by std dev) followed by
      either robust Z-score (median/MAD × 1.4826) or standard Z-score scaling.
      Drops zero-variance and NaN/Inf columns. Returns gene-aligned DataFrame
      ready for correlation.

  plot_correlation(final_corr_df, method, prefix, ...)
      Hierarchically clustered heatmap (seaborn clustermap, correlation metric,
      average linkage) with auto-scaled colorbar (diverging for mixed-sign data,
      sequential otherwise). Saves both PNG and PDF.

  correlation_qc_report(spearman_df, pearson_df, ...)
      Prints a structured QC report: DEG counts, correlation distribution
      statistics (mean, std, fraction > 0.5, > 0.7, < 0), and best-match per
      cluster with discriminability delta. Saves a histogram figure.

  correlation_between_h5ads(h5ad1, h5ad2, group_by1, group_by2, ...)
      Master function implementing the full cross-dataset concordance pipeline:
        1. Pseudobulk aggregation of both datasets (log1p pseudobulk means)
        2. DEG-based feature selection (nominal or FDR; union or intersection)
        3. Variance filtering and scaling
        4. Spearman correlation (unscaled pseudobulk, rank-based)
        5. Pearson correlation (robust Z-scored pseudobulk)
        6. Visualisation and QC report
      Returns (spearman_df, pearson_df).

  NOTE: utils_correlation.py also imports `pge` for pb_agg_by_cluster(),
  pearson_corr(), and spearman_corr(). See note above regarding pge access.
  Also requires: adjustText (pip install adjustText).


================================================================================
EXECUTION ORDER
================================================================================

All scripts are prefixed with a two-digit step number indicating execution
order. Run them sequentially. Each step consumes outputs from the previous one.

  config.yaml                              — shared configuration (paths, params)
  utils.py                                 — utility functions (imported by step 03)
  utils_correlation.py                     — correlation utilities (imported by step 04)
  01_cellranger_count.smk                  — FASTQ → gene × cell count matrices
  02_cellranger_annotate.smk               — automated cell annotation (10x Cloud)
  03_qc_preprocessing_annotation.py       — QC, normalisation, clustering, annotation
  04_annotation_concordance_AMPPD.py      — cross-dataset annotation concordance
  05_pseudobulk_de_dreamlet.R             — pseudobulk differential expression + fgsea
  06_gsea_clusterProfiler.R               — targeted GSEA with custom gene sets (GO/KEGG)

To run the Snakemake steps (on an HPC with SLURM):
  snakemake -s 01_cellranger_count.smk     --configfile config.yaml --cores 8
  snakemake -s 02_cellranger_annotate.smk  --configfile config.yaml --cores 8

Jupyter notebooks (.ipynb) can be executed interactively or via:
  jupyter nbconvert --to notebook --execute <notebook>.ipynb

R notebooks (steps 05–06) use an R kernel in Jupyter. Alternatively, extract
the R cells and run as standard .R scripts in an R session.


================================================================================
SCRIPT-TO-RESULT MAPPING
================================================================================

This table identifies which script produces each result in the manuscript.
"Figure X" refers to figure panels in the published article.

  Script                                   Outputs / Figure Panels
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  01_cellranger_count.smk                  Raw count matrices (.h5); deposited
                                           as primary data in data repository.

  02_cellranger_annotate.smk               Per-sample automated cell type
                                           annotation CSVs (cell_types.csv).

  03_qc_preprocessing_annotation.py       - QC metrics per sample (nCount_RNA,
                                             percent_mito, doublet rate)
                                           - UMAP of all cells coloured by
                                             cell type (Figure: UMAP panel)
                                           - Cell type composition barplots
                                             per genotype (Figure: composition)
                                           - Pearson correlation matrix across
                                             Leiden clusters vs reference atlases
                                           - Output: 2026_New_Annot1.h5ad
                                             (annotated, QC-filtered AnnData)

  04_annotation_concordance_AMPPD.py      - Pseudobulk Pearson & Spearman
                                             correlation heatmaps: miBRAIN vs
                                             AMP-PD/PPMI postmortem brain
                                             (Figure: annotation concordance)
                                           - Output CSVs:
                                             AMPPD_Pearson_Correlation.csv
                                             AMPPD_Spearman_Correlation.csv

  05_pseudobulk_de_dreamlet.R             - Variance partition plot per cell type
                                           - Voom mean-variance trend plots
                                           - Differential expression results for
                                             all contrasts (dreamlet 1.9):
                                               E3 vs Control
                                               E4 vs Control
                                               E4 vs E3
                                               A53T (pooled) vs Control
                                           - DEG summary tables:
                                               Summary_DEGs_E3vsCntrl.csv
                                               Summary_DEGs_E4vsCntrl.csv
                                               Summary_DEGs_E4vsE3.csv
                                           - Volcano plots per cell type per
                                             contrast (Figure: volcano panels)
                                           - Cell type specificity heatmap
                                             (Figure: specificity heatmap)
                                           - fgsea pathway enrichment (KEGG,
                                             GO:BP, GO:MF) per contrast
                                             (Figure: pathway bubble plots)
                                           - Output CSV:
                                               E3vsCntrl_Neurons_GOBP_Enrichment.csv
                                           - Saved R objects:
                                               miBRAIN_CLASS_cova_Diff.rds
                                               miBRAIN_dreamlet_degs_all_clusters.rds
                                               markers_raw.rds
                                               markers_clean.rds

  06_gsea_clusterProfiler.R               - Targeted GSEA (gseGO) for curated
                                             GO term sets in Neurons and
                                             Astrocytes (Figure: GSEA enrichment
                                             plots, 3-panel per pathway)
                                           - Pathways queried: proteostasis /
                                             autophagy, ubiquitin-proteasome,
                                             ER stress, synaptic vesicle cycle,
                                             postsynaptic organisation, lipid
                                             metabolism, endosomal-lysosomal
                                             trafficking, reactive astrocyte
                                             markers (A1/A2)


