  Number_of_cells_per_sample_ct
  Metadata.csv


================================================================================
CONFIGURATION
================================================================================

All file paths, sample identifiers, and analysis parameters for steps 01–02
are centralised in config.yaml. Before executing the Snakemake rules, update
the following fields to match your local environment:

  cellranger_count.REFERENCE    — path to GRCh38-2024-A reference directory
  cellranger_count.FASTQ_PATH   — path to raw FASTQ files
  cellranger_count.output_path  — desired output directory

Python scripts (steps 03–04) contain HPC-specific absolute paths at the top
of each notebook. Search for '/sc/arion/' and replace with your local paths
before executing.

R scripts (steps 05–06) contain a setwd() call at the top of each notebook.
Update to your working directory. GMT file paths must also be updated.


================================================================================
REPRODUCIBILITY NOTES
================================================================================

- Session information (package versions) is printed at the start of each
  notebook via session_info.show() (Python) and sessionInfo() (R).
- Random seeds are fixed: Python seed = 20210224; R set.seed(42) and
  set.seed(20210224) in relevant cells.
- Parallel processing uses BiocParallel::SnowParam() with worker counts
  specified per cell (6–12 workers). Adjust to available cores.
- Cell Ranger 9.0.1 automated cell annotation requires a 10x Genomics Cloud
  token (--tenx-cloud-token-path). A valid account is needed for step 02.
  This step is optional; manual annotation is performed in step 03.


